OL,3,CWidow of footballer who died from
OL,4,Cdementia calls for ban on heading ball
OL,6,FHis widow, Amanda Kopel, believes his
OL,7,Fdiagnosis was due to brain trauma
OL,8,Fcaused by repeated collisions with
OL,9,Fother players' heads while attempting
OL,10,Fto head the ball during matches, and
OL,11,Fheading the ball thousands of times
OL,12,Fduring decades of training.
OL,14,FShe said: "Frankie and I should be
OL,15,Fcelebrating today and looking forward
OL,16,Fto the rest of our lives together,
OL,17,Finstead I've been grieving his loss
OL,18,Fand mourning him for 10 years.
