OL,3,CWidow of footballer who died from
OL,4,Cdementia calls for ban on heading ball
OL,6,F"Football has to change because the
OL,7,Fgame is a long, slow, certain killer
OL,8,Fwhile heading the ball is part of it.
OL,10,F"The game is called football not
OL,11,Fheadball and the rules have to change.
OL,13,F"Nobody should head a ball `
OL,14,Fparticularly children. Frankie loved
OL,15,Fthe game but we never imagined for a
OL,16,Fmoment it was so damaging."
OL,18,FThe couple married in 1969 and lived
OL,19,Ftogether in Kirriemuir, Angus, but Mr
OL,20,FKopel was diagnosed with dementia in
OL,21,F2008 and died on April 16 2014.
