OL,3,CWidow of footballer who died from
OL,4,Cdementia calls for ban on heading ball
OL,6,FAfter his diagnosis, Mrs Kopel
OL,7,Fcollaborated with lobby group Heading
OL,8,FOut, founded by ex-journalist Mike
OL,9,FEdwards, who gave up his career at STV
OL,10,Fto care for his mother when she was
OL,11,Fdiagnosed with dementia, and who is
OL,12,Fcalling for an end to heading the ball
OL,13,Fby 2030.
OL,15,FThe organisation cited findings of an
OL,16,Facademic study which revealed that
OL,17,Ffootballers are three-and-a-half times
OL,18,Fmore likely to receive a diagnosis of
OL,19,Fa neuropathological disease like
OL,20,Fdementia, and five times more likely
OL,21,Fif they were a defender.
