OL,3,CWidow of footballer who died from
OL,4,Cdementia calls for ban on heading ball
OL,6,FIt said: "Reducing heading at this
OL,7,Flevel can support the development of
OL,8,Fmore skilful players who are able to
OL,9,Fstay on the ball when in possession,
OL,10,Fcontributing to the improved technical
OL,11,Fability of our young players.
OL,13,F"We also want to mitigate against any
OL,14,Fpotential risks that may be linked to
OL,15,Fheading the ball while research is
OL,16,Fongoing in this area."
